Migration.Name: Blood group should be a BP attribute #752

Step.SQLStatement: UPDATE C_BPartner SET Gender = (SELECT MAX(CASE WHEN Gender = 'Female' THEN 'F' WHEN Gender = 'Male' THEN 'M' ELSE NULL END) FROM HR_Employee WHERE C_BPartner_ID = C_BPartner.C_BPartner_ID)
UPDATE C_BPartner SET BloodGroup = (SELECT MAX(replace(BloodGroup, ' ', '')) FROM HR_Employee WHERE C_BPartner_ID = C_BPartner.C_BPartner_ID)
UPDATE C_BPartner SET Birthday = (SELECT MAX(Birthday) FROM HR_Employee WHERE C_BPartner_ID = C_BPartner.C_BPartner_ID)
UPDATE C_BPartner SET PlaceOfBirth = (SELECT MAX(PlaceOfBirth) FROM HR_Employee WHERE C_BPartner_ID = C_BPartner.C_BPartner_ID)
UPDATE C_BPartner SET FathersName = (SELECT MAX(FathersName) FROM HR_Employee WHERE C_BPartner_ID = C_BPartner.C_BPartner_ID)
